The Nigeria Police Force (NPF), Plateau  Command has confirmed the collapse of a two-storey building at Butcher Street, Terminus Market in Jos North Local Government Area of the state. DSP Terna Tyopev, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) of the command, who disclosed this in Jos said the incident occurred Sunday afternoon. Tyopev, however, said that neither was any life lost in the incident nor any casualty recorded. He said officers and men of the command had condoned off the affected area and investigations into the cause of disaster had commenced.